<PageTitle>Kinds of Exoplanets</PageTitle>

<h1 style="font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif; text-align: center;">Kind of Exoplanets</h1>
<h2 style="font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;">What are the kind of exoplanets?</h2>

<p>Welcome to the fascinating realm of exoplanets! Across the vast expanses of the universe, we find an astonishing
    variety of planets beyond our own solar system. There are eight primary types of exoplanets that astronomers have
    identified: Terrestrial Planets, Gas Giants, Ice Giants, Super-Earths, Mini-Neptunes, Hot Jupiters, Ultra-Short
    Period Planets, and Rogue Planets. Each category represents a distinct class of celestial bodies, offering a
    tapestry of environments and compositions that challenge our understanding of planetary science.</p>

